<paragraph blockId="28.[189,310,1262,1288]" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,1309,1476]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authority="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete, 2017" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,381,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,381,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Astiella perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[392,483,1309,1335]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete, 2017" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[622,780,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="homolleae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[622,780,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. homolleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[791,882,1309,1335]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having a reduced corolla tube with the stamens always exserted beyond the corolla throat, but differs in having an annual habit (vs perennial), stipules with less and shorter fimbriae (2–4 fimbriae vs 4–8 and 
<quantity box="[924,1069,1379,1406]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="0.8">0.8–2.7 mm</quantity>
vs 
<quantity box="[1104,1201,1379,1406]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 mm</quantity>
long), a glabrous corolla tube on the inside (vs papillate with trichomes towards the base), and seeds elliptic in outline with granulate microsculpturing (vs seeds triangular in outline with a verruculate microsculpturing).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
