<subSubSection box="[189,1309,691,764]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,285,691,717]" box="[189,285,691,717]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,285,691,717]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,285,691,717]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1309,738,764]" box="[189,1309,738,764]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Humid forest; along forest trails; secondary savannas; laterite substrate; at 
<quantity box="[1066,1187,738,764]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="19.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="950.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1900 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,437,803,829]" box="[189,437,803,829]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,437,803,829]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,803,829]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1399,849,982]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
The species is known from 15 collections, of which two without locality. The number of locations is eight. The extent of occurrence is more than 
<quantity box="[776,905,885,911]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="km" value="20000.0">20,000 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[909,918,883,897]" fontSize="6" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">2</superScript>
; the area of occupancy equals 
<quantity box="[1303,1380,885,911]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="km" value="36.0">36 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[1383,1392,883,897]" fontSize="6" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">2</superScript>
. Throughout the species’ distribution range, there is a high human pressure on the natural habitats. The species is therefore classified as vulnerable: VU B2ab(i,ii,iii).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,303,1021,1047]" box="[189,303,1021,1047]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1021,1047]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1021,1047]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1399,1067,1235]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
The specimen 
<emphasis box="[366,482,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Lantz s.n.</emphasis>
could be included in 
<taxonomicName authority="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete, 2017" authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[751,878,1068,1094]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[751,878,1068,1094]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[889,979,1068,1094]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
although it has flowers with welldeveloped corolla tubes (
<quantity box="[489,639,1102,1129]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.6 mm</quantity>
long). Several other specimens collected on the Island of Nosy Mangabe (
<emphasis box="[316,463,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Carlson 179</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[478,619,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Cheek 1380</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[634,889,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Schatz &amp; Miller 2514</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[904,1171,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Schatz &amp; Villiers 1833</emphasis>
) could be included as well, but these can be distinguished from the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Groeninckx &amp; Janssens &amp; Smets &amp; Verstraete" authorityYear="2017" box="[839,965,1173,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis box="[839,965,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens by their glabrous leaves. Because of these discrepancies, these specimens were not included in the species description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
